;
; This script is part one of three. The others are BlackTh2.scr and BlackTh3.scr
; Blackthorn Forest, outside section. Entrance location: Mirdaal Garden.
; Seasonal Hunting Area: Summer. Difficulty: moderately to very difficult.
;
MLIST 36 206 40 7
MLIST 36 236 30 5
MLIST 36 245 30 3
; shadow rat
; crimson mistwraith
; bloodscourge
MLIST 50 60 25 5
MLIST 50 61 25 5
MLIST 50 62 25 3
MLIST 50 63 25 3
; flagellent
; heart hound
; darkweaver
; black unicorn
VARIABLE CAVEIN
VARIABLE JABITEMVAL1
VARIABLE JABITEMVAL2
VARIABLE JABITEMVAL3
VARIABLE JABITEMVAL4
VARIABLE JABITEMVAL5
VARIABLE JABADJ1
VARIABLE JABADJ2
VARIABLE JABADJ3
VARIABLE MONSTERALERT
VARIABLE MONSTERTIME
; REGION 15 DEFINITIONS
REGIONDEF 15 WEATHER
REGIONDEF 15 SEASONS
REGIONDEF 15 TIME
REGIONDEF 15 WINTERTEMP 2
REGIONDEF 15 SUMMERTEMP 70
REGIONDEF 15 SPRINGTEMP 55
REGIONDEF 15 AUTUMNTEMP 55
REGIONDEF 15 PRECIPITATION 1
REGIONDEF 15 TELEPORT DISALLOWED
REGIONDEF 15 SUMMONING ALLOWED
REGIONDEF 15 DEPART 96
;
MACRO 69
IFPREVERB RETREAT -1
   IFVAR MONINROOM > PLRSINROOM
      SKILLCHECK 10 -10 DUMMY1
      IFVAR DISGUISED = 1
         SPELL 250
         EQUAL DUMMY1 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
      ELSE
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You try and retreat, but there are too many attackers.
         ECHO OTHERS %N tries frantically to get away from %h attackers, almost to the point of flailing.
         EQUAL ROUNDTIME 2
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 0
      IFVAR DISGUISED = 1
         IFVAR MONINROOM > 1
            ECHO ALL Sensing a hidden presence, your foe searches by normal and arcane means.
            SPELL 250
            ECHO PLAYER You have been discovered!
            ECHO OTHERS %N has been discovered!
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
; This version of the Garden overrides the base one as long as the Forest's season is in effect.
; Main change is to the room description, and an exit (the arch) has been added.
;
NUMBER 905
NAME Mirdaal, Garden
*DESCRIPTION_START
Ages ago a very large cavern near the surface collapsed, leaving a space
open to the sky and weather which the people of Mirdaal turned into a
garden. The pebble path to the north is strewn with debris and once-manicured
hedges threaten to obscure it completely with drooping leaves and branches.
The western door leads back underground. Along the southern wall, a profusion
of strange creepers and vines have grown wildly fast, forming a tall archway.
Through the arch, shadowy movement is visible where only the stone wall
should be.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT N 903
ITEM 0 340
EXIT ABOVE 2115
; hedges
ITEM 1 66 ADJ1=25 ADJ2=449 VAL2=904 UNLOCKED
; black peeling door
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The thick confusion of broken branches and sharp thorns makes it nearly
impossible to tell where one hedge ends and another begins. Small rustlings
and whispering chitters emanate from well within the fortress of tangled growth.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFTOUCH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You prick yourself on some nasty thorns you didn't see through the thick foliage.
   ECHO OTHERS %N grimaces as %s pricks %iself on some nasty thorns in the hedge.
ENDIF
ITEM 2 60 ADJ1=404 ADJ2=707 ADJ3=784 VAL2=1200 
; blackened thorny vine arch (leading into Blackthorn Forest)
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
The entrance is framed by thick vines that have twined together to form an
archway. They bristle with three-inch-long, black thorns.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO GROUP The thorny vines of the arch twitch as you pass, as if tempted to snare you rather than let you by.
   ECHO OTHGROUP %P goes through the arch.
   MOVEGROUP 1200
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 2
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER You remember hearing about a dark mythical grove called Blackthorn
      ECHO PLAYER Forest. Dangerous creatures dwell within, both caretakers and also,
      ECHO PLAYER perhaps, prisoners. The vines forming the arch match the description
      ECHO PLAYER of those from which the place is said to derive its name.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1200
NAME Bramble Archway
REGION 15
FOREST
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
A fitful wind gusts through the twining vines and branches, cleansing the
musty smell of the Garden from the air and bringing the scents of an ancient
forest. The sensation of being watched is very strong, but it is impossible
to tell who or what is watching. Perhaps it is the trees themselves...
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 1201
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=404 ADJ2=707 ADJ3=784 VAL2=905 
; blackened thorny vine arch (leading back out into the Mirdaal Garden)
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The entrance is framed by thick vines that have twined together to form an
archway. They bristle with three-inch-long, black thorns.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO GROUP The thorny vines of the arch twitch as you pass, as if tempted to snare you rather than let you by.
   ECHO OTHGROUP %P goes through the arch.
   MOVEGROUP 905
ENDIF
ITEM 1 63 VAL2=1210 
; crevice (leading to Quicksilver Pond)
IFPREVERB GO 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO GROUP You quietly make your way down the crevice.
   MOVEGROUP 1211
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Who or what were the people of Mirdaal? And why did they vanish?
      ECHO PLAYER This forest seems almost like a larger entity than merely trees.
      ECHO PLAYER If this place has opened here before, it might hold those answers...
      ECHO PLAYER ...or it might have swallowed them up entirely.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1201
NAME Dark Stream
REGION 15
FOREST
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
The muted sound of swiftly flowing water can be heard from somewhere deep
in the underbrush nearby.  The rushing of the stream almost drowns out the
other noises of the forest, but other signs of life make themselves apparent
in the quick movements glimpsed out of the corner of the eye.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1200
EXIT SE 1202
EXIT W 1204
EXIT SW 1205
IFVERB LISTEN -1
   ECHO PLAYER %C The dense plant life all around muffles and misdirects the sound of the hidden stream, making it impossible to pinpoint the location.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1202
NAME Silent Shade
REGION 15
FOREST
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
An expectant hush falls over this tiny clearing as the rustling of the leaves
disturbed by passage subsides. Distant sounds of the forest barely reach the
ear from the edges, but only a few paces within this meadow all is uncannily
still. Even the great Blackthorn trees that surround the glade are unmoving,
casting motionless dappled shade over the lush grass.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 1201
EXIT SW 1203
IFENTRY -1
   IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
      ECHO PLAYER The unearthly quiet subdues all sound in this place.
      SPELL 219
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The sound of your own breathing is loud in your ears.
   ECHO OTHERS %N seems to be straining to hear something.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The silence here is so profound that even your incantation is swallowed up.
   ECHO OTHERS %N's incantation is swallowed up in the profound silence.
   EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER It is said that what one tree in a forest hears, it whispers elsewhere to all of its kin.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1203
NAME Barrow Downs
REGION 15
PLAIN
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
Six small hills disturb the otherwise level surface of the ground here, too 
evenly spaced and uniformly shaped to be natural formations. They are arranged 
in a clear pattern, with five smaller mounds surrounding a larger one in the
center. No entrances are visible, and the dense underbrush shows that the area
has been relatively undisturbed for a very long time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1202
ITEM 0 916 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=149
; large grassy mound
EXTEND 0 surrounded by five smaller ones
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
This central mound is roughly two hundred feet in diameter, twice the size of 
the ones around it. Tall, wiry grass covers the entire hill, softening outlines
and hiding any evidence of how or when it was fashioned.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR WEIGHTWEQ > 250
      DISBAND
      ECHO PLAYER You clamber up the side of the largest hill, the dirt shifting beneath your weight.
      ECHO OTHERS %N clambers up the side of the largest hill, kicking down a few pebbles on the way.
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER When you reach the top of the mound, the ground beneath you suddenly gives way!
      ECHO OTHERS When %N reaches the top of the mound, the ground beneath %i suddenly gives way!
      MOVE 1233
      ; into Burial Chamber
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
      AFFECT 1233
      ECHO ALL %N tumbles through a hole in the ceiling, landing with a muffled thud.
      DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 30 You fall fifty feet onto a hard stone and dirt floor.
      POSITION LAY
      RANDOM MONSTERALERT 1 50 0
      IFVAR MONSTERALERT < 10
         PLREVENT 2
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO ALL A chilling voice rasps, "You shall pay for desecrating my tomb and disturbing my rest."
         GENMON 16
         ; lich
         GENMON 98
         GENMON 98
         ; shadow guardian
         AFFECT 1203
      ENDIF
      AFFECT 1203
   ENDIF
   IFVAR WEIGHTWEQ < 251
      DISBAND
      ECHO PLAYER You climb up the side of the central mound.
      ECHO OTHERS %N climbs up the side of the central mound.
      MOVE 1234
      ; to Atop a Hill
      AFFECT 1234
      ECHO OTHERS %N climbs up from the base of the mound.
      AFFECT 1203
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 0
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER You remember that a barrow mound it a sealed burial chamber for someone of
      ECHO PLAYER great status or importance. They are built from the base upwards, with the
      ECHO PLAYER final opening to be covered being the one at the very apex of the mound.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DIG -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You unearth some bodies buried here long ago... who are unhappy about being disturbed.
   ECHO OTHERS %N unearths some bodies buried here long ago... who are unhappy about being disturbed.
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
   GENMON 182 
   ; greater skeleton
   GENMON 183 
   ; greater ghoul
   GENMON 53 
   ; greater wight
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1204
NAME Deadly Vines
REGION 15
FOREST
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
The remains of a solitary traveller lie tangled in the crushing embrace of
coiling brambles, pierced in countless places by the daggerlike thorns. In
some places the vines are as thick as a man's wrist, and seem to have erupted
from the ground with unnatural swiftness to seize the hapless individual.
Strangely, other forest life flits about amongst the vines unharmed.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1201
EXIT SE 1205
ITEM 0 664 ADJ1=146 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=150 
; gnarled dark gray vine
EXTEND 0 wound around a crumbling skeleton
ITEM 1 390 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=415 ADJ3=347 
; old worn white skeleton
EXTEND 1 still clutching the rusty hilt of a broken sword
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Knotted and curled around each other, these vines seem to be fiercer versions 
of similar plants found throughout the Forest. They have grown out mysteriously
from a patch of otherwise identical brambles that climb a nearby Blackthorn tree.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Although tiny scavengers have long ago picked the bones clean, it is clear that
larger predators left the body undisturbed. The skeleton has gradually sunken
into the dirt under the weight its own bones and the enwrapping vines. A few
corroded bits of armor glint here and there, showing that no one took anything
from the remains, but left everything with the person where he fell.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB PUNCH 0
   ECHO PLAYER These vines hit back, as you discover to your dismay.
   ECHO OTHERS These vines hit back, as %N discovers to %h dismay.
   DAMAGEPLR SLASH 5 You step backward hurriedly as they lash out at you.
ENDIF
IFVERB THUMP 0
   ECHO PLAYER The vines seem annoyed when you thump on them, stabbing you!
   ECHO OTHERS The vines seem annoyed and move so they stab %N!
   DAMAGEPLR SLASH 10 You notice they deliberately moved to ensure you would stab yourself.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB KICK 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The vines seize your ankle and tug, sending you sprawling!
   ECHO OTHERS As %N tries to kick the vines, they grab %h ankle and send %i sprawling!
   DAMAGEPLR SLASH 10 Sharp thorns jab you as the vines grab hold.
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF
IFVERB PULL 0
   ECHO PLAYER The vines wrap around your wrist and pull back in response!
   ECHO OTHERS The vines grab %N and pull back as %N tugs on them.
   DAMAGEPLR SLASH 5 Sharp thorns jab you as the vines grab hold.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB BREAK 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The vines discourage you from breaking them by striking back at you!
   ECHO OTHERS The vines beat %N away from them with a furious lashing of thorny tendrils!
   DAMAGEPLR SLASH 25 Whip-thin tendrils slash stingingly against your arms and face.
ENDIF
IFVERB LIGHT 0
   ECHO PLAYER The vines recoil violently, and then retaliate!
   ECHO OTHERS The vines recoil violently as %N tries to burn them, and then retaliate!
   DAMAGEPLR BURN 50 Some of the singed leaves spatter burning, acidic sap on you.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB POKE 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You gingerly reach out to touch the vines, predictably jabbing your finger.
   ECHO OTHERS %N gingerly reaches out to touch the vines, predictably jabbing %h finger.
   DAMAGEPLR SLASH 2 You recoil from the sharp pain.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SNIFF 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The slender, green-black leaves emit a faint bittersweet scent of mingled wintergreen and musk.
   ECHO ALL %N carefully leans close to the vines and inhales deeply.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TAP 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Something seems to glance at you curiously, as if you had briefly caught its attention.
   ECHO OTHERS The bones clatter and clack for a few moments before quieting again when %N taps them.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER The skeleton is of human size and proportions, but so crumbled by time that further identification is impossible.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1205
NAME Tree of Bones
REGION 15
FOREST
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
Polished bones of all shapes and sizes dangle from a huge Witchwood tree,
showing stark ivory and white against the dark gray bark and deep violet
leaves. The bones have been carefully cleaned and hung from thin leather
thongs, though exactly who might have done this is hard to say. They rattle
softly when the breeze stirs them in an eerie melancholy music.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1201
EXIT NW 1204
EXIT S 1207
ITEM 0 229 ADJ1=329 ADJ2=7 
; towering ancient tree
ITEM 1 233 ADJ1=241 ADJ2=170 ADJ3=973 
; polished ivory colored bones
EXTEND 1 hung from the branches of the tree
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Rough, iron-gray bark contrasts with the smooth amethyst hue of the glossy
foliage. The leaves are long and thin, tapering to narrow points, and deeply
curved into the shape of dark crescent moons that shimmer in the light. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Bones of every shape and size sway from slender leather cords, from giant
skulls to tiny fingerbones. Those that have begun to crumble are carefully
reinforced with delicate wire of silver, copper, and gold.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The quiet clatter of the bones blends with the mournful tune of the wind.
   ECHO OTHERS %N listens thoughtfully to %h surroundings.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
   CLEARVERB
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER %cYou scramble up some of the branches and into the tree.%c
   ECHO OTHERS %c%N scrambles up some of the branches and disappears into the tree.%c
   MOVE 1206
   AFFECT 1206
   ECHO OTHERS %c%N scrambles up the trunk of the tree onto a large branch.%c
   AFFECT 1205
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TAP 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The bones all over the tree rattle and clack when you tap just one of them.
   ECHO OTHERS The bones all over the tree rattle and clack when %N taps just one of them.
ENDIF
IFVERB PULL 1
   RANDOM MONSTERALERT 1 50 0
   IFVAR MONSTERALERT < 10
      ECHO ALL The entire tree shudders in response, the clattering of the bones echoing loudly across the clearing.
      ECHO ALL Something comes rushing toward you, summoned by the sound!
      GENMON 62
      ; darkweaver
      GENMON 63
      ; black unicorn
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB GET 1
   RANDOM MONSTERALERT 1 50 0
   IFVAR MONSTERALERT < 10
      ECHO ALL The entire tree shudders in response, the clattering of the bones echoing loudly across the clearing.
      ECHO ALL Something comes rushing toward you, summoned by the sound!
      GENMON 62
      ; darkweaver
      GENMON 63
      ; black unicorn
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB STEAL 1
   RANDOM MONSTERALERT 1 50 0
   IFVAR MONSTERALERT < 10
      ECHO ALL The entire tree shudders in response, the clattering of the bones echoing loudly across the clearing.
      ECHO ALL Something comes rushing toward you, summoned by the sound!
      GENMON 62
      ; darkweaver
      GENMON 63
      ; black unicorn
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 0
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER The bones hung from the branches are not so much an obsession with this particular
      ECHO PLAYER tree, but rather a sign of reverence for the Forest as a whole. In keeping with
      ECHO PLAYER that deep respect, it is unlikely the denizens would attempt any violence amongst
      ECHO PLAYER its boughs. By the same token, they are likely to defend it fiercely, however.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Not all of the bones are human. Many of Andor's races are represented here, from
      ECHO PLAYER aelfen to drakin to goblin. Even more unsettling are the ones from no species you
      ECHO PLAYER have ever seen before. One thing is clear, however: none of bones are from creatures
      ECHO PLAYER that seem to be native here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1206
NAME Among the Bones
REGION 15
JUNGLE
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
*DESCRIPTION_START
Jounced by the movement of the branches, a human skull spins around on the end
of its tether, mocking anyone nearby equally with its empty leer. Drooping
leaves brush one's face with an almost sinister caress. Down below, the
creatures of the forest seem reluctant to climb this particular tree and do
not attempt to pursue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 1205
ITEM 0 352 ADJ1=1132 ADJ2=170 ADJ3=164 
; pale ivory human skull
EXTEND 0 dangling from a leather thong
ITEM 1 607 ADJ1=348 ADJ2=156 
; wide heavy branch
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
It might be more comforting somehow if it were carelessly hung here dirty
and neglected, showing that whoever did this was a mere savage. But as it is,
this skull - and the other bones - give the unsettling impression that the
caretakers are both intelligent and thorough. The grinning lower jawbone has
been carefully reattached with thin silvery wire.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Wide enough to stand or sit upon with relative comfort, this sturdy branch
still has a rounded shape that makes the wise watch their balance. Leaves
whisper and bones rattle with the slightest jar.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB GAZE -1
   ECHO PLAYER Hollow eyesockets meet your gaze at every turn.
ENDIF
IFVERB KISS 0
   ECHO PLAYER For an instant, ghostly lips meet yours and return the kiss!
   ECHO OTHERS %N looks a bit startled.
ENDIF
IFVERB CURSE 0
   ECHO ALL A raspy voice cackles, "Too late! I already am cursed!"
ENDIF
IFVERB KICK 0
   ECHO PLAYER The motion causes you to lose your balance and tumble out of the tree.
   ECHO OTHERS %N loses %h balance on the branch and tumbles out of the tree.
   MOVE 1205
   POSITION LAY
   AFFECT 1205
   ECHO OTHERS Look out below! %N tumbles out of the tree and crashes to the ground.
   AFFECT 1206
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LISTEN 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER In a disembodied whisper, you hear the words, "As I am, so shall you be..."
   ECHO OTHERS %N listens to the skull, and then stares at it for a moment.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You give the skull a little push, causing it to whirl faster in its erratic dance.
   ECHO OTHERS %N gives the skull a little push, causing it to whirl faster in its erratic dance.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TAP 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO ALL %N taps the human skull.%c
   ECHO ALL The slack jawbone sways slightly up and down when jarred, making it look like the skull is laughing at your predicament.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 0
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Compared to many of the other bones, this one looks very recent.
      ECHO PLAYER There seem to be gaps in the age of the bones here - from ancient and
      ECHO PLAYER decaying, to old, to very new, with not much transition in between.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB JUMP -1
   ECHO ALL The bones hanging all around you clatter and clack loudly when you shake them.
   AFFECT 1205
   ECHO ALL Something large moves in the tree overhead, causing the bones to jump and clatter loudly.
   AFFECT 1206
ENDIF
IFVERB THUMP 1
   ECHO ALL The bones hanging all around you clatter and clack loudly when you shake them.
   AFFECT 1205
   ECHO ALL Something large moves in the tree overhead, causing the bones to jump and clatter loudly.
   AFFECT 1206
ENDIF
IFVERB KICK 1
   ECHO ALL The bones hanging all around you clatter and clack loudly when you shake them.
   AFFECT 1205
   ECHO ALL Something large moves in the tree overhead, causing the bones to jump and clatter loudly.
   AFFECT 1206
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1207
NAME Small Rise
REGION 15
PLAIN
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 36
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
Long red-gold grass rustles and bows as one ascends to the crest of this
small hill. The trees thin here slightly, allowing a view of the rest of
the Forest stretched out below, brooding yet beautiful. Northward is a
strange tree festooned with bones, while wisps of fog and the flash of
bright water come from the south.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1205
EXIT SE 1208
EXIT SW 1210
IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You hear the breeze whispering softly through the tall grass.
   ECHO OTHERS %N turns %h face toward the breeze and listens for a moment.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You pause for a moment and take in the panoramic view before you.
   ECHO OTHERS %N casts %h gaze across the area.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Free of any obstructions to vision, this strikes you as an excellent place
      ECHO PLAYER to survey your surroundings from. Perhaps if you concentrated a little bit
      ECHO PLAYER more closely, you might see even farther.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
   RANDOM DUMMY2 1 8 0
   IFVAR DUMMY2 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze far off into the distance...
      ECHO OTHERS %N gazes far off into the distance.
