;
; This script is part two of three. The others are BlackTh1.scr and BlackTh3.scr
; Blackthorn Forest, inner section. Entrance location: altar in Mysterious Shrine.
; Seasonal Hunting Area: Summer. Difficulty: very difficult.
;
NUMBER 1215
NAME Dark Heart of the Forest
FOREST
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
*DESCRIPTION_START
Unguessably ancient trees loom tall and dark all around, yet even these are
dwarfed by the truly magnificent Blackthorn tree that towers above them. An
aura of power surrounds it, brooding and ominous. Nothing else grows in the
shadow of its dense, twisting limbs; even the otherwise omnipresent grasses
keep a respectful distance. Climbing rose vines grow in profusion among the
branches of several of the surrounding trees, forming a dimly lit archway
nearly hidden by deep blue flowers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=707 ADJ2=820 ADJ3=784 VAL2=1216
; thorny rose vine arch (leading to Inner Sanctum)
ITEM 1 72 ADJ1=210 ADJ2=264 VAL2=1218
; narrow rocky opening (leading down to Below the Root)
EXTEND 1 among the roots of an enormous tree
ITEM 2 229 ADJ1=1123 ADJ2=25 ADJ3=706
; majestic black thorn tree
EXTEND 2 with rough, charcoal gray bark and emerald green leaves
ITEM 3 1317 ADJ1=668 ADJ2=468 ADJ3=828
; leaning golden hued grass
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The vines are so dark a green they are almost black, with leaves that are 
only slightly lighter in hue. The strongly scented blooms range from deep
violet to rich cobalt blue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Many of the rocks around the base of the tree have been shattered by time
and the elements. One especially large boulder has cracked down the center,
split by a massive tree root, revealing a crevice leading underground.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Flickers of deep green light edge the glossy leaves as they move in the wind.
The tips of the lower branches bow almost to the ground in places, brushing
against the broken stones. Heavy, gnarled roots radiate out in all directions
from the massive trunk, creating a maze of mysterious openings.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
The blades of grass are tall and slender. They bow in graceful waves as the
breeze passes over them, as though giving homage to the trees around whose
trunks they grow. The warm green-gold color seems to be the natural hue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER An opening catches your eye, amongst the roots of the central tree.
   ECHO OTHERS %N casts %h gaze across the area.
ENDIF
IFVERB SNIFF -1
   ECHO PLAYER The mingled scents of the forest are particularly pleasant here, spiced with the perfume of the roses.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You pick your way over the broken stones down into the opening.
   ECHO OTHERS %N picks %h way over the broken stones down into the opening.
   DISBAND
   MOVE 1218
   AFFECT 1218
   ECHO OTHERS %N arrives through the narrow opening.
   AFFECT 1215
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 2
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Old folktales speak of grandfather trees, with whom all the other trees in
      ECHO PLAYER in the forest around them are said to be linked. Some say they hold within
      ECHO PLAYER them the essence of the land, eternal embodiments of the cycle of nature.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN 2
   ECHO PLAYER A deep, resonant voice speaks into your mind...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER "Thus the Wheel turns,
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER  In peace and in strife.
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER  Life becomes death, and..."
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The voice fades from your mind, the final words indistinguishable.
ENDIF
IFSAY Death_becomes_life
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER A slow, rumbling voice echoes in your mind, "The Wheel turns ever onward..." Your surroundings begin to blur and fade into a deep green illumination.
   ECHO OTHERS %N is suffused in a brightening deep green light. When it fades, %N is gone.
   MOVE 1214
   AFFECT 1214
   ECHO OTHERS %N appears in a flare of deep green-black light.
   AFFECT 1213
   GMMSG %N just transported back to the Blackthorn altar from the Heart of the Forest.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1216
NAME Inner Sanctum
REGION 15
JUNGLE
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 68
*DESCRIPTION_START
Screened from outside view by the boughs of the living walls is a small
but exquisite enclosed garden. Myriad tiny luminous night-creatures live 
in the branches, lighting the space beneath with a soft bluegreen glow. 
Lush indigo moss covers the paths and open areas, springy and comfortable.
In the center, rambling black-leaved vines bearing deep violet roses grow
around a clear pool, where silvery fish dart, creating flashes of blue and
green reflection. A small door is barely visible in the western wall, almost
completely hidden from view by the hanging vines.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=707 ADJ2=820 ADJ3=784 VAL2=1215
; thorny rose vine arch (leading to Dark Heart of the Forest)
ITEM 1 944 ADJ1=87 ADJ2=107 VAL1=5000 VAL2=1217 VAL3=728 CLOSED
; dark ebony door (into Home of Korrvuz)
ITEM 2 324 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=91 ; pool
EXTEND 2 surrounded by midnight roses
PUT 2 198 ADJ1=67 ADJ2=56 VAL2=999
; cool clear water, in the pond
ITEM 3 274 ADJ1=1243
; indigo rose
ITEM 4 418 ADJ1=209 
; mysterious house
EXTEND 4 woven from living growth of the forest
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The vines are so dark a green they are almost black, with leaves that are 
only slightly lighter in hue. The strongly scented blooms range from deep
violet to rich cobalt blue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The wood is unvarnished, yet undamaged by time or weather. The blackened
silver hinges and latch have been cast by an expert hand in the shape of
crows in flight.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The water smells pure and sweet. Delicate underwater plants sway gently in
a slight current from an unseen source, rooted in glittering black sand.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
Tall, slender Blackthorn saplings stand close together to shape the outer 
walls, their interwoven branches overhead forming the roof and eaves. Vines
and nightflowers twine amongst the trunks to fill any gaps. Everywhere
throughout the living tapestry are shifting images of unfamiliar places.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SNIFF -1
   ECHO PLAYER The cool air is filled with the smell of night-blooming flowers.
ENDIF
IFVERB GAZE -1
   ECHO PLAYER Perhaps it is a trick of the eye, but it seems impossible to tell the exact dimensions of the garden despite the walls.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You take a seat and relax on the thick, springy moss.
   ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat and relaxes on the thick, springy moss.
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF
IFVERB GAZE 2
   ECHO PLAYER The shimmering surface invites quiet contemplation, leaving you with a sense of pleasant melancholy as you come back out of your reverie.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER Animal people appear in legends around the world. In some cultures, the gods
      ECHO PLAYER take on forms that blend humanoid and beast. The Crow or Raven as a deity is
      ECHO PLAYER often viewed as one who brings change, and a trickster.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GET 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You reach down and take one of the dark blue roses.
   ECHO OTHERS %N reaches down and takes one of the dark blue roses.
   NEWITEM -1 274 ADJ1=1243
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1217
NAME Home of Korrvuz
REGION 15
INDOOR_GROUND
FIXED_LIGHT
BUY_SKINS
CHANNEL 68
*DESCRIPTION_START
The moss covering the floor here is a rich tapestry of deep reds and 
golds. Dark gray vines weave from ceiling to floor to form the inner 
walls, with especially large thorns projecting at places where shelves 
or skins are hung. Amber magelights held by angled branches shaped like 
sylized talons cast a warm, dim glow over the room. An ornately carved 
desk stands against one wall, across the room from the heavy cauldrons.
A strange being, resembling a humanoid raven, looks up expectantly.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 944 ADJ1=87 ADJ2=107 VAL1=5000 VAL2=1216 VAL3=728
; dark ebony door (out to Inner Sanctum)
ITEM 1 201 ADJ1=534 ADJ2=579 ADJ3=107
; ornate solid ebony desk
ITEM 2 1169 ADJ1=241 ADJ2=292
; polished silver cauldron
ITEM 3 1169 ADJ1=318 ADJ2=292
; tarnished silver cauldron
ITEM 4 1169 ADJ1=404 ADJ2=292
; blackened silver cauldron
ITEM 5 204 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=355
; small wooden sign
EXTEND 5 propped against a corner of the desk
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The wood is unvarnished, yet undamaged by time or weather. The blackened
silver hinges and latch have been cast by an expert hand in the shape of
crows in flight.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Various pieces of dead creatures are neatly arranged on the smooth desktop.
Small carvings of ravens and crows line the upper edge and run along the
length of the legs. The feet of the desk seem melded into the floor, as
though still rooted into the packed dirt floor beneath. A small, neatly
handwritten sign stands unobtrusively against one corner.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Large enough to climb into, this cauldron is similar to those used to dye
fabrics, although the strange vapors seething within are like nothing used
in any ordinary weaver's craftwork. The metal is polished to a high luster.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
Large enough to climb into, this cauldron is similar to those used to dye
fabrics, although the strange vapors seething within are like nothing used
in any ordinary weaver's craftwork. The metal is antiqued to a dull gray.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 4
Large enough to climb into, this cauldron is similar to those used to dye
fabrics, although the strange vapors seething within are like nothing used
in any ordinary weaver's craftwork. The metal is blacked to distinguish it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 5
Written in bold, flowing script are the words, "Use cauldrons, fifty gold."
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFSAY Nevermore
   ECHO PLAYER Korrvuz laughs at you!
   ECHO OTHERS Korrvuz laughs hoarsely at %N, greatly amused.
ENDIF
IFSAY Jabberwock
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz caws, "Beware the Jubjub bird, and shun the frumious Bandersnatch!"
ENDIF
; With due apologies to Lewis Carroll.
IFSAY Korrvuz?
   ECHO ALL The raven-man cocks his head and eyes %N curiously, then nods.
ENDIF
IFSAY Cauldron?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz bobs his head and caws, "Cauldrons change things. Each different."
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The raven-man points to the three cauldrons nearby.
ENDIF
IFSAY Greetings_Korrvuz
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz nods, pleased, and caws, "Greetings, %N. Welcome."
ENDIF
IFSAY Collect?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz gestures at the desk littered with skins and caws, "Yes. Collect parts."
ENDIF
IFSAY Blackthorn_Forest?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz bows his head reverantly and whispers, "Is heart of world. My home."
ENDIF
IFSAY Shadow_rat?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz hisses in disgust and caws, "Nasty little things. Much magic, though."
ENDIF
IFSAY Mistwraith?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz shrugs and caws, "Is spirit. Some say is kind of ghost."
ENDIF
IFSAY Bloodscourge?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz makes a disgusted noise and caws, "Crazy beast. Can't talk to."
ENDIF
IFSAY Flagellant?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz shudders, muttering, "Even crazier than Bloodscourge."
ENDIF
IFSAY Heart_hound?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz chuckles and caws, "Think of as very big guard dog."
ENDIF
IFSAY Darkweaver?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz flares his wings, cawing, "Very powerful. Worship Blackthorn Forest."
ENDIF
IFSAY Unicorn?
   ECHO ALL Korrvuz touches his forehead and caws, "Caretaker of Forest. Friend of darkweaver."
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 1
   ECHO PLAYER The raven-man ruffles his wings in annoyance and caws, "I collect. Careful."
   ECHO OTHERS The raven-man ruffles his wings in annoyance at %N and caws, "I collect. Careful."
ENDIF
; If this is done without saving the values below, weapons and armor lose their statistics.
