EXIT W 1228
ITEM 0 78 ADJ1=163 ADJ2=293 ADJ3=346 VAL2=1226
; huge slippery wet boulder (have to climb it, to Twisted Spire)
EXTEND 0 in the middle of the rapids
ITEM 1 411 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=84 ADJ3=202
; large damp mossy rock
EXTEND 1 barely visible above the rushing water
PUT 1 1082 ADJ1=299 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=29
; soggy dark blue moss (under the rock)
; Yes, they can take it, but they'll only get one per day.
ITEM 2 348 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=173
; small jagged stones
EXTEND 2 scattered among the larger rocks
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
It is, quite simply, an enormous chunk of granite that fell into the
river. The stream has worn away at a small crack in the rock, until
the boulder split roughly in half, the two sections forming a very
narrow, v-shaped archway.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
A particularly resiliant species of moss has managed to take up
residence on this good-sized rock. The water ebbs just often enough
to keep the plant wet, but not drown it completely.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Some of them might be semiprecious or even precious stones, glimpsed
temptingly through the foam. But the current is so strong they are
washed away before they can be grasped.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR AGI > 75
      ECHO PLAYER You duck beneath the raging water and claw your way back upstream.
      ECHO OTHERS %N claws %h way back upstream by clinging desperately to a boulder.
      MOVEGROUP 1226
      AFFECT 1226
      ECHO OTHERS %N struggles out of the stream through an unseen gap in the rubble.
      AFFECT 1227
   ENDIF
   IFVAR AGI < 76
      ECHO PLAYER The boulder is too slick for you to hold onto!
      ECHO OTHERS %N loses %h hold on the boulder and falls down into the rocks.
      DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 15 You fall down bruisingly amongst the jagged rocks.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1228
NAME Behemoth's Maw
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
MINEA
*DESCRIPTION_START
A gigantic cavern meets the eye, a welcome sight after the close quarters
leading into it. A broad river cuts across the area, its surface placid
in the dim glow of the tiny phosphorescent creatures living within. The
entrance where the water flows in is studded with particularly large
spikes of stone on both ceiling and floor, making it resemble the gaping
mouth of some enormous fanged beast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1227
EXIT SW 1229
ITEM 0 1675 ADJ1=348
; wide river (into Within the Well)
EXTEND 0 that meanders through the mouth of the cavern
PUT 0 198 ADJ1=67 ADJ2=56 VAL2=999
; cool clear water (in the river)
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Miniscule creatures that glow soft blue, green, and violet dart about
in the clear water. Each one emits barely enough light to illuminate
itself, but together they create an ever-changing tapestry of cool
radiance beneath the river's surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER The current is stronger than you realized, and you are swept away!
   ECHO OTHERS %N steps into the river and is swept away into the darkness.
   MOVE 1231
   AFFECT 1231
   ECHO OTHERS You sense that something else has just been transported in here with you.
   AFFECT 1228
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1229
NAME River's End
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
MINEA
*DESCRIPTION_START
As wide as the river is, still it ends here, roaring down into the huge
sinkhole that nearly fills the chamber. A thin ledge rings the gigantic
opening, but there are no other exits other than the tunnel back along
the river, or the hole itself. Amazingly, there seem to be notches
carved in a spiral pattern along the sides of the shaft, leading down
into the watery darkness.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1228
ITEM 0 79 ADJ1=451 ADJ2=693 VAL2=1230
; enormous circular hole (to The Darkwell)
EXTEND 0 leading down into the shadowy depths
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
There is little to be seen other than dark stone and a thundering waterfall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB LISTEN -1
   ECHO PLAYER The deep roar of the waterfall reverberates through your body.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The thunderous waterfall drowns out your incantation.
   ECHO OTHERS %N seems to be saying something, but it is impossible to hear over the waterfall.
   EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1230
NAME The Darkwell
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
MONSTER_GROUP 50
CALL 69
MINEA
*DESCRIPTION_START
The weighty presence of the surrounding stone is strongly felt here, as
though the very earth strives to impress itself upon the awareness. Water
falls in a shimmering circular curtain through the hole up above. The
eternal rain has worn a ring-shaped moat around another, smaller opening
in the floor. A peculiar structure has been constructed over the pit,
molded out of the living rock, to form some kind of shrine.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 79 ADJ1=451 ADJ2=693 VAL2=1229
; enormous circular hole (to River's End)
EXTEND 0 leading up through the waterfall
ITEM 1 917 ADJ1=1038 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=312
; strange dark stone well (to Within the Well)
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
There is little to be seen other than dark stone and a thundering waterfall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
A rim of gleaming obsidian forms the base of the shrine, roughly as high as
a man's waist. An arch at each of the four cardinal directions allows water
that falls beyond the ring to flow down into the well. Tiny crystal chimes
dangle from the corners of the sharply peaked roof, their music mingling
with the loud roar of the waterfall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 1
   CLEARVERB
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER You step over the rim into the well, and feel yourself wrenched in every direction at once.
   ECHO OTHERS %N steps over the rim into the well, and vanishes utterly into the darkness.
   MOVE 1231
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
   AFFECT 1231
   ECHO OTHERS You sense that something else has just been transported in here with you.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL 1
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 3
      ECHO PLAYER How someone could have constructed this within the water's flow is a
      ECHO PLAYER mystery, but the reason it is here may not be. There is an elemental
      ECHO PLAYER feel to this place, as of something timeless, even sacred.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM => 99
     IFVAR ARCHNUM =< 121
       IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 300
          REMOVEITEM -1
          ECHO PLAYER You drop your gem into the well, where it vanishes into the darkness.
          ECHO OTHERS %N drops a small gem into the well and watches it swiftly vanish from sight.
       ENDIF
       IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 299
          REMOVEITEM -1
          ECHO PLAYER You drop your gem into the well. A cool wind whispers in your mind, "You have journeyed far to make your offering. I shall ease your travel home."
          ECHO OTHERS %N drops a gem into the well and vanishes in a cool autumn breeze.
          DISBAND
          MOVE 1215
          AFFECT 1215
          ECHO OTHERS A sudden breeze stirs up a whirlwind of fallen leaves, which coalesce into %N.
          AFFECT 1230
          GMMSG %N put a valuable gem in the well and was transported to the Dark Heart of the Forest.
       ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1231
NAME Within the Well
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
REGION 15
CHANNEL 68
OUTOFBODY
*DESCRIPTION_START
Black nothingness is everywhere, an utter and complete void. Within this
primal emptiness, strange sounds whisper at the edge of hearing. The
physical world has ceased to have much meaning. Vague suggestions of
once-animate shapes drift past, their presence felt rather than seen as
all senses strain to their utmost. There is no water, no stone, no light
or dark... even one's own body seems remote and unreachable in this place
that is both everywhere and nowhere at once.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1696 ADJ1=580
; still body 
; You must "go body" to get out of here. It's a bit of a puzzle.
EXTEND 0 drifting slowly through the void
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Something seems disturbingly familiar about the form, the clothing, the gear...
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY -1
   GMMSG %N was just transported Within the Well. There IS a way out, but they have to find it.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   DISBAND
   ECHO PLAYER You reach out towards your body, and with a sudden jolt, merge back into it!
   ECHO OTHERS You sense that something has just been transported out of this place.
   MOVE 1230
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
   POSITION LAY
   AFFECT 1230
   ECHO OTHERS %N wavers into view at the edge of the well, looking shaken.
   AFFECT 1231
ENDIF
IFVERB PONDER -1
   ECHO PLAYER Your thoughts tend to scatter, and you find it difficult to recall much.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
   ECHO PLAYER You realize with a start that you have been separated from your physical
   ECHO PLAYER body. Still linked to it by the thinnest of ethereal threads, you are not
   ECHO PLAYER quite what one would consider dead, but you are also barely alive.
ENDIF
